A callback 'missing return' bug happens when a block-bodied callback computes a value but never returns it, so callers get `undefined`.

Typical broken code:
```js
const ids = users.map(user => {
  user.id;
});
```

Fix it by returning the value, or by using an expression-bodied arrow function:
```js
const ids = users.map(user => {
  return user.id;
});

// or
const ids = users.map(user => user.id);
```

Another common case is `filter`:
```js
// broken
items.filter(item => {
  item.active;
});

// fixed
items.filter(item => {
  return item.active;
});
```

