assert.strictEqual(relativePath('/a/b', '/a/c'), '../c');
assert.strictEqual(relativePath('/a/b/c', '/a/b/c/d/e'), 'd/e');
assert.strictEqual(relativePath('/a/b/c', '/a/b'), '..');
assert.strictEqual(relativePath('/', '/a/b'), 'a/b');
assert.strictEqual(relativePath('/a/b', '/'), '../..');
assert.strictEqual(relativePath('/a/b/', '/a/b/c/'), 'c');
assert.strictEqual(relativePath('\\a\\b', '\\a\\c'), '../c');

assert.throws(() => relativePath('a/b', '/a/b'), /absolute/);
assert.throws(() => relativePath('/a/b', 'a/b'), /absolute/);
assert.throws(() => relativePath('', '/a/b'), /empty/);
assert.throws(() => relativePath(null, '/a/b'), /strings/);

console.log('All tests passed');
```

Notes:
- Returns `'.'` for the same normalized path.
- Treats trailing slashes as insignificant.
- Supports backslashes by normalizing `\\` to `/`.
- Assumes POSIX-style absolute paths after normalization; Windows drive letters/UNC paths are not handled by this version.
